Asked when they closed and she said at 7pm and I looked down at my phone and it was 7:02. All of us just gave her a disgusted look and walked away. Vale is one of my favorite lunch spots Downtown. I love the bowl concept. You pick a base, veggie, protein, sauce and toppings. You can be healthy and the menu and items available allow you to customize for almost every type of diet. I usually get a regular size bowl (I try to eat half and save the rest for later) but you could eat in all in one serving easily. Especially since it's so delicious, you won't want to stop eating! Today I got double veggie quinoa as my base, green beans and roasted brussel sprouts as my veg with double ancho pulled chicken. Topped off with sliced almonds and chipotle ranch dressing on the side. Perfect Friday lunch!

I needed food for my flight home and came across Vale Foods. I’m looking for a healthier option, and the selection does not disappoint😍 The server took my bewildered look and walked me through the options...I’m so excited to eat and share this bowl with my Crew😎

A couple of friends recommended this place to me knowing that I love fresh and healthy fast food options.  Here are a few reasons I liked it: 1.  Wide open floor plan. They can pack a lot of people in there and so it’s probably still a cool place to be when it’s very busy. 2. The options. There are SO many options! Normally, my husband has a hard time adjusting to a new healthy food place if I take him (he’s fairly picky) but even he smiled at some of the options available. Their drink options are plentiful as well. There is definitely something here for everyone.  Also, it looks as though they have a smoothie bar, which wasn’t open, but sounds heavenly. 3.  The food was really yummy.  Even the rice had diverse flavor profiles without an excess of sodium and that is always a plus. The teriyaki chicken was juicy and not overpowering in flavor either. It was extremely well-balanced.  Even though I only had three items and a scoop of guacamole, I ate til I was satisfied and didn’t feel too heavy nor was I let down in the flavor department at all! 4. They use cast-iron skillets to cook everything in!  So basically, there’s your boost of iron right there. I was pleasantly surprised with this little tidbit.

The location is great, the atmosphere is laid back and very modern, and the food is awesome too. I ate here for the first time about two weeks ago and the reason for the three stars is the lack of availability of certain ingredients. The day I went they were out of ancho chicken so my only option was to get the "chicken of the day" if I didn't want to pay extra for tuna/steak/shrimp etc. In addition, you pay extra for "boost" items such as feta, pesto, and guacamole. I opted for the spicy feta - clearly on the menu - but was met with a confused look, as if the girl had no idea that was even offered. The food is delicious but if I truly were to build my perfect bowl, it would cost nearly $20. When it says two bases, two proteins, and two veggies for $10, that covers the bare minimum.
